Given	I'm logged-in with valid credentials
And	I'm on Page 05 of Feet MRI
And I select 'Finding' radio button
When I select 'Tendinopathy' from the dropdown menu
Then 'Localizer' is enabled

When I click on the Localizer
Then 'Extraarticular localization' canvas opens

When I select 'Achilles tendon' on the canvas
And I close the canvas
Then 'Tendinopathy' checkbox is enabled
And 'Tear' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Tendinopathy' checkbox
Then 'Tendinopathy details' tab is enabled and selected by default
And 'Diffuse' radio button is enabled
And 'Focal' radio button is enabled
And 'T2w/PD hyperintensity' checkbox is enabled
And 'T1w hyperintensity' checkbox is enabled
And 'Thickening' checkbox is enabled
And 'Retrocalcaneal (subachilleal) bursitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Calcifying tendinitis' checkbox is enabled
And 'Intratendinous, soft tissue foci' checkbox is enabled
And 'Hypervascularization of the tendon' checkbox is enabled
And 'Osteitis of the tuber calcanei' checkbox is enabled
And 'Haglund deformity' checkbox is enabled
And 'Dorsal heel spur' checkbox is enabled
And 'Peritendinous edema' checkbox is enabled
And 'Differential diagnosis' dropdown menu is enabled

When I select 'Focal' radio button
Then 'Distance from Tuber calcanei' input field is enabled

When I select 'Thickening' checkbox
Then 'Convex anterior contour' checkbox is enabled
And 'Max. sagittal diameter' input field is enabled
And 'Fusiform contour (sagittal)' checkbox is enabled

When I select 'Dorsal heel spur' checkbox is enabled
Then 'Size' input field is enabled

When I select 'Peritendinous edema' checkbox
Then 'Edema in Kager's fat pad' checkbox is enabled
